In .NET 10, MAUI on Android moved to **edge-to-edge** rendering, which makes the old `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` ineffective. Here are your options:

---

### Option 1: Use `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (default)

MAUI's built-in keyboard scroll manager is enabled by default. Ensure your input is inside a `ScrollView` or that you haven't disabled it:

```xml
<ScrollView>
    <Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
        <!-- Messages list -->
        <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ... />
        <!-- Input bar -->
        <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1">
            <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
            <Button Text="Send" />
        </HorizontalStackLayout>
    </Grid>
</ScrollView>
```

---

### Option 2: Handle keyboard insets manually (recommended for chat UIs)

Listen for inset changes and adjust bottom padding:

```csharp
// In your Android platform code or a handler
#if ANDROID
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

public static void ApplyKeyboardInsets(ContentPage page)
{
    var activity = Platform.CurrentActivity;
    var rootView = activity?.Window?.DecorView?.RootView;
    if (rootView == null) return;

    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new InsetsListener(page));
}

class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    private readonly ContentPage _page;
    public InsetsListener(ContentPage page) => _page = page;

    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var bottomPadding = imeInsets.Bottom / DeviceDisplay.MainDisplayInfo.Density;

        _page.Dispatcher.Dispatch(() => _page.Padding = new Thickness(0, 0, 0, bottomPadding));

        return ViewCompat.OnApplyWindowInsets(v, insets);
    }
}
#endif
```

---

### Option 3: Force legacy behavior in `AndroidManifest.xml`

As a quick fix, you can opt out of edge-to-edge:

```xml
<activity
    android:name=".MainActivity"
    android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize"
    android:theme="@style/Maui.MainTheme" />
```

And in your `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);
    // Opt out of edge-to-edge to restore .NET 9 behavior
    AndroidX.Activity.EdgeToEdge.Disable(this);
}
```

---

**TL;DR:** Option 2 is the proper .NET 10 approach for chat UIs. Option 3 is the quickest migration path if you just want the old behavior back.
